[SN]TITLE[SN]
Lockerbie breakfast bar theft trailer traced in Wales

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A trailer carrying breakfast bars worth Â£45,000 which was stolen in southern Scotland has been recovered on an industrial estate in north Wales.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
It was taken from the lorry park at Johnstonebridge near Lockerbie in the early hours of Thursday morning.
Police confirmed the trailer had been found in Mold on Saturday but its load of Kellogg's cereal bars had gone.
They said they were keen to speak to anyone who may have seen the transporter on its journey south.
